cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB 

This paper is about improving named entity recognition (NER) systems using Wikipedia as an open knowledge base. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which covers topics related to natural language processing, including NER. The paper also involves machine learning models, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of Wikipedia as a knowledge base could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DB (Databases).
